    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>The capacity or tendency of a material to respond to light or similar radiation. Examples include inks, dyes, paper, fabric, glass, and other materials that undergo physical changes when exposed to light.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
